Text.Value: It's always the ones you least suspect.
Might be right. One sip and the world goes all fuzzy, like I'm dreaming - but awake.
Hells. Gortash isn't pulling his punches.
Not a clue. Just keep doing what we were doing, I guess.
Sentenced to hang, last I knew.
Had an uncle like that. Swore his outhouse was haunted.
They named Gortash Archduke yet?
My old bracers went missing - the ones Oloril sold me.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Here the guards are mentioning that things are getting stollen inside the fortress. That's a reference to the Flaming Fist Thief in the barracks.

Text.Value: Gortash? He's a man of action.
Hells if I know. I've been stuck down here for what seems like a tenday.
Why should he? She's a blasted traitor, no two ways about it. One of those Absolute cultists.
Make a godsdamn decision, for starters. The Council talks 'til their jaws near fall off, but nothing ever gets done.
Damn. Two more legs for smashing? Would love to see that thing in action.
What's the plan with the Grand Duke's counsellor?
Hear the news out of the foundry?
So, what? You're saying there could really be a dragon down there?
The sooner the better. If anyone can fix up this pigpen, it's him.
Hells if I know. Just saying that sometimes there's nothing stranger than truth.
What? Toobin finally get crushed by a Watcher?
Turns out there was a ghost in there, for real. Local wizard had to get rid of it.
Don't be daft. You probably left 'em at Sharess' Caress after a slug of Hoots' latest hooch.
Old Man Otto's been muttering in his sleep. Something about a dragon sleeping under Wyrm's Rock.
There's a thieving rat in the barracks, I'm telling you. Unless you think my good helm grew legs and walked off.
Doesn't he have family who could look after him? The fellow's a few haystalks short of a stack.
We've already got the Council. What can Gortash do that they can't?
Nah - heard they're making those metal beasts with four legs now 'stead of two.
Never saw it coming. Loyal to the city 'til the end, I figured.
You got any idea what we're supposed to do different what with Lord Gortash getting murdered?
It's all that gruel he's been getting. He's hungrier than a farm ox after ploughing.
I guess. With any luck, nobody upstairs will give us a thought for a full tenday. Maybe two.
That's some godsdamned poetry right there.
